Package: worldfoundry-retro-tools
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: World Foundry <packages@worldfoundry.org>
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Depends: mame,
 mame-tools,
 dasm,
 cc65,
 z80dasm,
 z80asm,
 radare2,
 binwalk,
 sox,
 binutils-m68k-linux-gnu
Recommends: ghidra,
 f9dasm,
 vgmstream,
 libvgm,
 xa65
Suggests: java-common
Homepage: https://worldfoundry.org/port-arcade/
Description: arcade reverse-engineering and porting toolchain
 Tooling for porting classic arcade ROMs to the World Foundry engine:
 MAME (debugger + tools), 6502/Z80/68k disassemblers and assemblers,
 radare2, binwalk, sox (audio conversion).
 .
 Recommends includes packages we ship ourselves (Ghidra repackaged
 from the Apache upstream, f9dasm, vgmstream, libvgm, xa65) — they're
 not in the Ubuntu archive but are available from the Foundry APT
 repo.
